  42 class TestDatetime64ArrayLikeComparisons:
  43     # Comparison tests for datetime64 vectors fully parametrized over
  44     #  DataFrame/Series/DatetimeIndex/DatetimeArray.  Ideally all comparison
  45     #  tests will eventually end up here.
  46 
  47     def test_compare_zerodim(self, tz_naive_fixture, box_with_array):
  48         # Test comparison with zero-dimensional array is unboxed
  49         tz = tz_naive_fixture
  50         box = box_with_array
  51         xbox = box_with_array if box_with_array is not pd.Index else np.ndarray
  52         dti = date_range("20130101", periods=3, tz=tz)
  53 
  54         other = np.array(dti.to_numpy()[0])
  55 
  56         dtarr = tm.box_expected(dti, box)
  57         result = dtarr <= other
  58         expected = np.array([True, False, False])
  59         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
  60         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)
  61 
  62     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
  63         "other",
  64         [
  65             "foo",
  66             -1,
  67             99,
  68             4.0,
  69             object(),
  70             timedelta(days=2),
  71             # GH#19800, GH#19301 datetime.date comparison raises to
  72             #  match DatetimeIndex/Timestamp.  This also matches the behavior
  73             #  of stdlib datetime.datetime
  74             datetime(2001, 1, 1).date(),
  75             # GH#19301 None and NaN are *not* cast to NaT for comparisons
  76             None,
  77             np.nan,
  78         ],
  79     )
  80     def test_dt64arr_cmp_scalar_invalid(self, other, tz_naive_fixture, box_with_array):
  81         # GH#22074, GH#15966
  82         tz = tz_naive_fixture
  83 
  84         rng = date_range("1/1/2000", periods=10, tz=tz)
  85         dtarr = tm.box_expected(rng, box_with_array)
  86         assert_invalid_comparison(dtarr, other, box_with_array)
  87 
  88     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
  89         "other",
  90         [
  91             list(range(10)),
  92             np.arange(10),
  93             np.arange(10).astype(np.float32),
  94             np.arange(10).astype(object),
  95             pd.timedelta_range("1ns", periods=10).array,
  96             np.array(pd.timedelta_range("1ns", periods=10)),
  97             list(pd.timedelta_range("1ns", periods=10)),
  98             pd.timedelta_range("1 Day", periods=10).astype(object),
  99             pd.period_range("1971-01-01", freq="D", periods=10).array,
 100             pd.period_range("1971-01-01", freq="D", periods=10).astype(object),
 101         ],
 102     )
 103     def test_dt64arr_cmp_arraylike_invalid(self, other, tz_naive_fixture):
 104         # We don't parametrize this over box_with_array because listlike
 105         #  other plays poorly with assert_invalid_comparison reversed checks
 106         tz = tz_naive_fixture
 107 
 108         dta = date_range("1970-01-01", freq="ns", periods=10, tz=tz)._data
 109         assert_invalid_comparison(dta, other, tm.to_array)
 110 
 111     def test_dt64arr_cmp_mixed_invalid(self, tz_naive_fixture):
 112         tz = tz_naive_fixture
 113 
 114         dta = date_range("1970-01-01", freq="h", periods=5, tz=tz)._data
 115 
 116         other = np.array([0, 1, 2, dta[3], pd.Timedelta(days=1)])
 117         result = dta == other
 118         expected = np.array([False, False, False, True, False])
 119         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 120 
 121         result = dta != other
 122         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, ~expected)
 123 
 124         msg = "Invalid comparison between|Cannot compare type|not supported between"
 125         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 126             dta < other
 127         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 128             dta > other
 129         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 130             dta <= other
 131         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 132             dta >= other
 133 
 134     def test_dt64arr_nat_comparison(self, tz_naive_fixture, box_with_array):
 135         # GH#22242, GH#22163 DataFrame considered NaT == ts incorrectly
 136         tz = tz_naive_fixture
 137         box = box_with_array
 138         xbox = box if box is not pd.Index else np.ndarray
 139 
 140         ts = pd.Timestamp.now(tz)
 141         ser = pd.Series([ts, pd.NaT])
 142 
 143         obj = tm.box_expected(ser, box)
 144 
 145         expected = pd.Series([True, False], dtype=np.bool_)
 146         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
 147 
 148         result = obj == ts
 149         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)

 152 class TestDatetime64SeriesComparison:
 153     # TODO: moved from tests.series.test_operators; needs cleanup
 154 
 155     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
 156         "pair",
 157         [
 158             (
 159                 [pd.Timestamp("2011-01-01"), NaT, pd.Timestamp("2011-01-03")],
 160                 [NaT, NaT, pd.Timestamp("2011-01-03")],
 161             ),
 162             (
 163                 [pd.Timedelta("1 days"), NaT, pd.Timedelta("3 days")],
 164                 [NaT, NaT, pd.Timedelta("3 days")],
 165             ),
 166             (
 167                 [pd.Period("2011-01", freq="M"), NaT, pd.Period("2011-03", freq="M")],
 168                 [NaT, NaT, pd.Period("2011-03", freq="M")],
 169             ),
 170         ],
 171     )
 172     @pytest.mark.parametrize("reverse", [True, False])
 173     @pytest.mark.parametrize("dtype", [None, object])
 174     def test_nat_comparisons(self, dtype, index_or_series, reverse, pair):
 175         box = index_or_series
 176         l, r = pair
 177         if reverse:
 178             # add lhs / rhs switched data
 179             l, r = r, l
 180 
 181         left = Series(l, dtype=dtype)
 182         right = box(r, dtype=dtype)
 183         # Series, Index
 184 
 185         expected = Series([False, False, True])
 186         tm.assert_series_equal(left == right, expected)
 187 
 188         expected = Series([True, True, False])
 189         tm.assert_series_equal(left != right, expected)
 190 
 191         expected = Series([False, False, False])
 192         tm.assert_series_equal(left < right, expected)
 193 
 194         expected = Series([False, False, False])
 195         tm.assert_series_equal(left > right, expected)
 196 
 197         expected = Series([False, False, True])
 198         tm.assert_series_equal(left >= right, expected)
 199 
 200         expected = Series([False, False, True])
 201         tm.assert_series_equal(left <= right, expected)
 202 
 203     def test_comparison_invalid(self, tz_naive_fixture, box_with_array):
 204         # GH#4968
 205         # invalid date/int comparisons
 206         tz = tz_naive_fixture
 207         ser = Series(range(5))
 208         ser2 = Series(pd.date_range("20010101", periods=5, tz=tz))
 209 
 210         ser = tm.box_expected(ser, box_with_array)
 211         ser2 = tm.box_expected(ser2, box_with_array)
 212 
 213         assert_invalid_comparison(ser, ser2, box_with_array)

 215     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
 216         "data",
 217         [
 218             [Timestamp("2011-01-01"), NaT, Timestamp("2011-01-03")],
 219             [Timedelta("1 days"), NaT, Timedelta("3 days")],
 220             [Period("2011-01", freq="M"), NaT, Period("2011-03", freq="M")],
 221         ],
 222     )
 223     @pytest.mark.parametrize("dtype", [None, object])
 224     def test_nat_comparisons_scalar(self, dtype, data, box_with_array):
 225         if box_with_array is tm.to_array and dtype is object:
 226             # dont bother testing ndarray comparison methods as this fails
 227             #  on older numpys (since they check object identity)
 228             return
 229 
 230         xbox = box_with_array if box_with_array is not pd.Index else np.ndarray
 231 
 232         left = Series(data, dtype=dtype)
 233         left = tm.box_expected(left, box_with_array)
 234 
 235         expected = [False, False, False]
 236         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
 237         tm.assert_equal(left == NaT, expected)
 238         tm.assert_equal(NaT == left, expected)
 239 
 240         expected = [True, True, True]
 241         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
 242         tm.assert_equal(left != NaT, expected)
 243         tm.assert_equal(NaT != left, expected)
 244 
 245         expected = [False, False, False]
 246         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
 247         tm.assert_equal(left < NaT, expected)
 248         tm.assert_equal(NaT > left, expected)
 249         tm.assert_equal(left <= NaT, expected)
 250         tm.assert_equal(NaT >= left, expected)
 251 
 252         tm.assert_equal(left > NaT, expected)
 253         tm.assert_equal(NaT < left, expected)
 254         tm.assert_equal(left >= NaT, expected)
 255         tm.assert_equal(NaT <= left, expected)

 257     @pytest.mark.parametrize("val", [datetime(2000, 1, 4), datetime(2000, 1, 5)])
 258     def test_series_comparison_scalars(self, val):
 259         series = Series(date_range("1/1/2000", periods=10))
 260 
 261         result = series > val
 262         expected = Series([x > val for x in series])
 263         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)

 265     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
 266         "left,right", [("lt", "gt"), ("le", "ge"), ("eq", "eq"), ("ne", "ne")]
 267     )
 268     def test_timestamp_compare_series(self, left, right):
 269         # see gh-4982
 270         # Make sure we can compare Timestamps on the right AND left hand side.
 271         ser = pd.Series(pd.date_range("20010101", periods=10), name="dates")
 272         s_nat = ser.copy(deep=True)
 273 
 274         ser[0] = pd.Timestamp("nat")
 275         ser[3] = pd.Timestamp("nat")
 276 
 277         left_f = getattr(operator, left)
 278         right_f = getattr(operator, right)
 279 
 280         # No NaT
 281         expected = left_f(ser, pd.Timestamp("20010109"))
 282         result = right_f(pd.Timestamp("20010109"), ser)
 283         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
 284 
 285         # NaT
 286         expected = left_f(ser, pd.Timestamp("nat"))
 287         result = right_f(pd.Timestamp("nat"), ser)
 288         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
 289 
 290         # Compare to Timestamp with series containing NaT
 291         expected = left_f(s_nat, pd.Timestamp("20010109"))
 292         result = right_f(pd.Timestamp("20010109"), s_nat)
 293         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
 294 
 295         # Compare to NaT with series containing NaT
 296         expected = left_f(s_nat, pd.Timestamp("nat"))
 297         result = right_f(pd.Timestamp("nat"), s_nat)
 298         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
 299 
 300     def test_dt64arr_timestamp_equality(self, box_with_array):
 301         # GH#11034
 302         xbox = box_with_array if box_with_array is not pd.Index else np.ndarray
 303 
 304         ser = pd.Series([pd.Timestamp("2000-01-29 01:59:00"), "NaT"])
 305         ser = tm.box_expected(ser, box_with_array)
 306 
 307         result = ser != ser
 308         expected = tm.box_expected([False, True], xbox)
 309         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)
 310 
 311         result = ser != ser[0]
 312         expected = tm.box_expected([False, True], xbox)
 313         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)
 314 
 315         result = ser != ser[1]
 316         expected = tm.box_expected([True, True], xbox)
 317         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)
 318 
 319         result = ser == ser
 320         expected = tm.box_expected([True, False], xbox)
 321         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)
 322 
 323         result = ser == ser[0]
 324         expected = tm.box_expected([True, False], xbox)
 325         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)
 326 
 327         result = ser == ser[1]
 328         expected = tm.box_expected([False, False], xbox)
 329         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)

 332 class TestDatetimeIndexComparisons:
 333 
 334     # TODO: moved from tests.indexes.test_base; parametrize and de-duplicate
 335     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
 336         "op",
 337         [operator.eq, operator.ne, operator.gt, operator.lt, operator.ge, operator.le],
 338     )
 339     def test_comparators(self, op):
 340         index = tm.makeDateIndex(100)
 341         element = index[len(index) // 2]
 342         element = Timestamp(element).to_datetime64()
 343 
 344         arr = np.array(index)
 345         arr_result = op(arr, element)
 346         index_result = op(index, element)
 347 
 348         assert isinstance(index_result, np.ndarray)
 349         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(arr_result, index_result)
 350 
 351     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
 352         "other",
 353         [datetime(2016, 1, 1), Timestamp("2016-01-01"), np.datetime64("2016-01-01")],
 354     )
 355     def test_dti_cmp_datetimelike(self, other, tz_naive_fixture):
 356         tz = tz_naive_fixture
 357         dti = pd.date_range("2016-01-01", periods=2, tz=tz)
 358         if tz is not None:
 359             if isinstance(other, np.datetime64):
 360                 # no tzaware version available
 361                 return
 362             other = localize_pydatetime(other, dti.tzinfo)
 363 
 364         result = dti == other
 365         expected = np.array([True, False])
 366         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 367 
 368         result = dti > other
 369         expected = np.array([False, True])
 370         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 371 
 372         result = dti >= other
 373         expected = np.array([True, True])
 374         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 375 
 376         result = dti < other
 377         expected = np.array([False, False])
 378         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 379 
 380         result = dti <= other
 381         expected = np.array([True, False])
 382         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 383 
 384     @pytest.mark.parametrize("dtype", [None, object])
 385     def test_dti_cmp_nat(self, dtype, box_with_array):
 386         if box_with_array is tm.to_array and dtype is object:
 387             # dont bother testing ndarray comparison methods as this fails
 388             #  on older numpys (since they check object identity)
 389             return
 390 
 391         xbox = box_with_array if box_with_array is not pd.Index else np.ndarray
 392 
 393         left = pd.DatetimeIndex(
 394             [pd.Timestamp("2011-01-01"), pd.NaT, pd.Timestamp("2011-01-03")]
 395         )
 396         right = pd.DatetimeIndex([pd.NaT, pd.NaT, pd.Timestamp("2011-01-03")])
 397 
 398         left = tm.box_expected(left, box_with_array)
 399         right = tm.box_expected(right, box_with_array)
 400 
 401         lhs, rhs = left, right
 402         if dtype is object:
 403             lhs, rhs = left.astype(object), right.astype(object)
 404 
 405         result = rhs == lhs
 406         expected = np.array([False, False, True])
 407         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
 408         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)
 409 
 410         result = lhs != rhs
 411         expected = np.array([True, True, False])
 412         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
 413         tm.assert_equal(result, expected)
 414 
 415         expected = np.array([False, False, False])
 416         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
 417         tm.assert_equal(lhs == pd.NaT, expected)
 418         tm.assert_equal(pd.NaT == rhs, expected)
 419 
 420         expected = np.array([True, True, True])
 421         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
 422         tm.assert_equal(lhs != pd.NaT, expected)
 423         tm.assert_equal(pd.NaT != lhs, expected)
 424 
 425         expected = np.array([False, False, False])
 426         expected = tm.box_expected(expected, xbox)
 427         tm.assert_equal(lhs < pd.NaT, expected)
 428         tm.assert_equal(pd.NaT > lhs, expected)
 429 
 430     def test_dti_cmp_nat_behaves_like_float_cmp_nan(self):
 431         fidx1 = pd.Index([1.0, np.nan, 3.0, np.nan, 5.0, 7.0])
 432         fidx2 = pd.Index([2.0, 3.0, np.nan, np.nan, 6.0, 7.0])
 433 
 434         didx1 = pd.DatetimeIndex(
 435             ["2014-01-01", pd.NaT, "2014-03-01", pd.NaT, "2014-05-01", "2014-07-01"]
 436         )
 437         didx2 = pd.DatetimeIndex(
 438             ["2014-02-01", "2014-03-01", pd.NaT, pd.NaT, "2014-06-01", "2014-07-01"]
 439         )
 440         darr = np.array(
 441             [
 442                 np_datetime64_compat("2014-02-01 00:00Z"),
 443                 np_datetime64_compat("2014-03-01 00:00Z"),
 444                 np_datetime64_compat("nat"),
 445                 np.datetime64("nat"),
 446                 np_datetime64_compat("2014-06-01 00:00Z"),
 447                 np_datetime64_compat("2014-07-01 00:00Z"),
 448             ]
 449         )
 450 
 451         cases = [(fidx1, fidx2), (didx1, didx2), (didx1, darr)]
 452 
 453         # Check pd.NaT is handles as the same as np.nan
 454         with tm.assert_produces_warning(None):
 455             for idx1, idx2 in cases:
 456 
 457                 result = idx1 < idx2
 458                 expected = np.array([True, False, False, False, True, False])
 459                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 460 
 461                 result = idx2 > idx1
 462                 expected = np.array([True, False, False, False, True, False])
 463                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 464 
 465                 result = idx1 <= idx2
 466                 expected = np.array([True, False, False, False, True, True])
 467                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 468 
 469                 result = idx2 >= idx1
 470                 expected = np.array([True, False, False, False, True, True])
 471                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 472 
 473                 result = idx1 == idx2
 474                 expected = np.array([False, False, False, False, False, True])
 475                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 476 
 477                 result = idx1 != idx2
 478                 expected = np.array([True, True, True, True, True, False])
 479                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 480 
 481         with tm.assert_produces_warning(None):
 482             for idx1, val in [(fidx1, np.nan), (didx1, pd.NaT)]:
 483                 result = idx1 < val
 484                 expected = np.array([False, False, False, False, False, False])
 485                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 486                 result = idx1 > val
 487                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 488 
 489                 result = idx1 <= val
 490                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 491                 result = idx1 >= val
 492                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 493 
 494                 result = idx1 == val
 495                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 496 
 497                 result = idx1 != val
 498                 expected = np.array([True, True, True, True, True, True])
 499                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 500 
 501         # Check pd.NaT is handles as the same as np.nan
 502         with tm.assert_produces_warning(None):
 503             for idx1, val in [(fidx1, 3), (didx1, datetime(2014, 3, 1))]:
 504                 result = idx1 < val
 505                 expected = np.array([True, False, False, False, False, False])
 506                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 507                 result = idx1 > val
 508                 expected = np.array([False, False, False, False, True, True])
 509                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 510 
 511                 result = idx1 <= val
 512                 expected = np.array([True, False, True, False, False, False])
 513                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 514                 result = idx1 >= val
 515                 expected = np.array([False, False, True, False, True, True])
 516                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 517 
 518                 result = idx1 == val
 519                 expected = np.array([False, False, True, False, False, False])
 520                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 521 
 522                 result = idx1 != val
 523                 expected = np.array([True, True, False, True, True, True])
 524                 tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)
 525 
 526     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
 527         "op",
 528         [operator.eq, operator.ne, operator.gt, operator.ge, operator.lt, operator.le],
 529     )
 530     def test_comparison_tzawareness_compat(self, op, box_with_array):
 531         # GH#18162
 532         box = box_with_array
 533 
 534         dr = pd.date_range("2016-01-01", periods=6)
 535         dz = dr.tz_localize("US/Pacific")
 536 
 537         dr = tm.box_expected(dr, box)
 538         dz = tm.box_expected(dz, box)
 539 
 540         msg = "Cannot compare tz-naive and tz-aware"
 541         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 542             op(dr, dz)
 543 
 544         if box is pd.DataFrame:
 545             tolist = lambda x: x.astype(object).values.tolist()[0]
 546         else:
 547             tolist = list
 548 
 549         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 550             op(dr, tolist(dz))
 551         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 552             op(dr, np.array(tolist(dz), dtype=object))
 553         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 554             op(dz, dr)
 555 
 556         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 557             op(dz, tolist(dr))
 558         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 559             op(dz, np.array(tolist(dr), dtype=object))
 560 
 561         # The aware==aware and naive==naive comparisons should *not* raise
 562         assert np.all(dr == dr)
 563         assert np.all(dr == tolist(dr))
 564         assert np.all(tolist(dr) == dr)
 565         assert np.all(np.array(tolist(dr), dtype=object) == dr)
 566         assert np.all(dr == np.array(tolist(dr), dtype=object))
 567 
 568         assert np.all(dz == dz)
 569         assert np.all(dz == tolist(dz))
 570         assert np.all(tolist(dz) == dz)
 571         assert np.all(np.array(tolist(dz), dtype=object) == dz)
 572         assert np.all(dz == np.array(tolist(dz), dtype=object))
 573 
 574     @pytest.mark.parametrize(
 575         "op",
 576         [operator.eq, operator.ne, operator.gt, operator.ge, operator.lt, operator.le],
 577     )
 578     def test_comparison_tzawareness_compat_scalars(self, op, box_with_array):
 579         # GH#18162
 580         dr = pd.date_range("2016-01-01", periods=6)
 581         dz = dr.tz_localize("US/Pacific")
 582 
 583         dr = tm.box_expected(dr, box_with_array)
 584         dz = tm.box_expected(dz, box_with_array)
 585 
 586         # Check comparisons against scalar Timestamps
 587         ts = pd.Timestamp("2000-03-14 01:59")
 588         ts_tz = pd.Timestamp("2000-03-14 01:59", tz="Europe/Amsterdam")
 589 
 590         assert np.all(dr > ts)
 591         msg = "Cannot compare tz-naive and tz-aware"
 592         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 593             op(dr, ts_tz)
 594 
 595         assert np.all(dz > ts_tz)
 596         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 597             op(dz, ts)
 598 
 599         # GH#12601: Check comparison against Timestamps and DatetimeIndex
 600         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
 601             op(ts, dz)

 607     @pytest.mark.parametrize(

 615     @pytest.mark.filterwarnings("ignore:Converting timezone-aware:FutureWarning")

 671         tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result, expected)

 674         expected = np.array([True] * 10)

1216         # GH#10699
1217         vec = DatetimeIndex(
1218             [
1219                 Timestamp("2000-01-05 00:15:00"),
1220                 Timestamp("2000-01-31 00:23:00"),

1229         vec = tm.box_expected(vec, box_with_array)
1230         vec_items = vec.squeeze() if box_with_array is pd.DataFrame else vec
1231 
1232         # DateOffset relativedelta fastpath
1233         relative_kwargs = [
1234             ("years", 2),
1235             ("months", 5),
1236             ("days", 3),
1237             ("hours", 5),
1238             ("minutes", 10),
1239             ("seconds", 2),
1240             ("microseconds", 5),
1241         ]
1242         for i, kwd in enumerate(relative_kwargs):
1243             off = pd.DateOffset(**dict([kwd]))
1244

1246             expected = tm.box_expected(expected, box_with_array)
1247             tm.assert_equal(expected, vec + off)
1248 
1249             expected = DatetimeIndex([x - off for x in vec_items])
1250             expected = tm.box_expected(expected, box_with_array)
1251             tm.assert_equal(expected, vec - off)
1252 
1253             off = pd.DateOffset(**dict(relative_kwargs[: i + 1]))
1254 
1255             expected = DatetimeIndex([x + off for x in vec_items])
1256             expected = tm.box_expected(expected, box_with_array)
1257             tm.assert_equal(expected, vec + off)
1258 
1259             expected = DatetimeIndex([x - off for x in vec_items])
1260             expected = tm.box_expected(expected, box_with_array)
1261             tm.assert_equal(expected, vec - off)
1262             msg = "(bad|unsupported) operand type for unary"
1263             with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
1264                 off - vec

1320         self, box_with_array, n, normalize, cls_and_kwargs
1321     ):
1322         # GH#10699
1323         # assert vectorized operation matches pointwise operations
1324 
1325         if isinstance(cls_and_kwargs, tuple):
1326             # If cls_name param is a tuple, then 2nd entry is kwargs for
1327             # the offset constructor
1328             cls_name, kwargs = cls_and_kwargs
1329         else:
1330             cls_name = cls_and_kwargs
1331             kwargs = {}
1332

1334             "WeekOfMonth",
1335             "LastWeekOfMonth",
1336             "FY5253Quarter",
1337             "FY5253",
1338         ]:
1339             # passing n = 0 is invalid for these offset classes
1340             return
1341 
1342         vec = DatetimeIndex(
1343             [
1344                 Timestamp("2000-01-05 00:15:00"),

1355         vec_items = vec.squeeze() if box_with_array is pd.DataFrame else vec
1356 
1357         offset_cls = getattr(pd.offsets, cls_name)
1358 
1359         with warnings.catch_warnings(record=True):
1360             # pandas.errors.PerformanceWarning: Non-vectorized DateOffset being
1361             # applied to Series or DatetimeIndex
1362             # we aren't testing that here, so ignore.
1363             warnings.simplefilter("ignore", PerformanceWarning)
1364 
1365             offset = offset_cls(n, normalize=normalize, **kwargs)
1366

1558     def test_dt64_series_arith_overflow(self):
1559         # GH#12534, fixed by GH#19024
1560         dt = pd.Timestamp("1700-01-31")
1561         td = pd.Timedelta("20000 Days")
1562         dti = pd.date_range("1949-09-30", freq="100Y", periods=4)
1563         ser = pd.Series(dti)
1564         msg = "Overflow in int64 addition"
1565         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
1566             ser - dt
1567         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
1568             dt - ser
1569         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
1570             ser + td
1571         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
1572             td + ser
1573 
1574         ser.iloc[-1] = pd.NaT
1575         expected = pd.Series(
1576             ["2004-10-03", "2104-10-04", "2204-10-04", "NaT"], dtype="datetime64[ns]"
1577         )
1578         res = ser + td
1579         tm.assert_series_equal(res, expected)
1580         res = td + ser
1581         tm.assert_series_equal(res, expected)
1582 
1583         ser.iloc[1:] = pd.NaT
1584         expected = pd.Series(
1585             ["91279 Days", "NaT", "NaT", "NaT"], dtype="timedelta64[ns]"
1586         )
1587         res = ser - dt
1588         tm.assert_series_equal(res, expected)
1589         res = dt - ser
1590         tm.assert_series_equal(res, -expected)

1592     def test_datetimeindex_sub_timestamp_overflow(self):
1593         dtimax = pd.to_datetime(["now", pd.Timestamp.max])
1594         dtimin = pd.to_datetime(["now", pd.Timestamp.min])
1595 
1596         tsneg = Timestamp("1950-01-01")
1597         ts_neg_variants = [
1598             tsneg,
1599             tsneg.to_pydatetime(),
1600             tsneg.to_datetime64().astype("datetime64[ns]"),
1601             tsneg.to_datetime64().astype("datetime64[D]"),
1602         ]
1603 
1604         tspos = Timestamp("1980-01-01")
1605         ts_pos_variants = [
1606             tspos,
1607             tspos.to_pydatetime(),
1608             tspos.to_datetime64().astype("datetime64[ns]"),
1609             tspos.to_datetime64().astype("datetime64[D]"),
1610         ]
1611         msg = "Overflow in int64 addition"
1612         for variant in ts_neg_variants:
1613             with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
1614                 dtimax - variant
1615 
1616         expected = pd.Timestamp.max.value - tspos.value
1617         for variant in ts_pos_variants:
1618             res = dtimax - variant
1619             assert res[1].value == expected
1620 
1621         expected = pd.Timestamp.min.value - tsneg.value
1622         for variant in ts_neg_variants:
1623             res = dtimin - variant
1624             assert res[1].value == expected
1625 
1626         for variant in ts_pos_variants:
1627             with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
1628                 dtimin - variant

1630     def test_datetimeindex_sub_datetimeindex_overflow(self):
1631         # GH#22492, GH#22508
1632         dtimax = pd.to_datetime(["now", pd.Timestamp.max])
1633         dtimin = pd.to_datetime(["now", pd.Timestamp.min])
1634 
1635         ts_neg = pd.to_datetime(["1950-01-01", "1950-01-01"])
1636         ts_pos = pd.to_datetime(["1980-01-01", "1980-01-01"])
1637 
1638         # General tests
1639         expected = pd.Timestamp.max.value - ts_pos[1].value
1640         result = dtimax - ts_pos
1641         assert result[1].value == expected
1642 
1643         expected = pd.Timestamp.min.value - ts_neg[1].value
1644         result = dtimin - ts_neg
1645         assert result[1].value == expected
1646         msg = "Overflow in int64 addition"
1647         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
1648             dtimax - ts_neg
1649 
1650         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
1651             dtimin - ts_pos
1652 
1653         # Edge cases
1654         tmin = pd.to_datetime([pd.Timestamp.min])
1655         t1 = tmin + pd.Timedelta.max + pd.Timedelta("1us")
1656         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
1657             t1 - tmin
1658 
1659         tmax = pd.to_datetime([pd.Timestamp.max])
1660         t2 = tmax + pd.Timedelta.min - pd.Timedelta("1us")
1661         with pytest.raises(OverflowError, match=msg):
1662             tmax - t2

1911     def test_operators_datetimelike_with_timezones(self):
1912         tz = "US/Eastern"
1913         dt1 = Series(date_range("2000-01-01 09:00:00", periods=5, tz=tz), name="foo")
1914         dt2 = dt1.copy()
1915         dt2.iloc[2] = np.nan
1916 
1917         td1 = Series(pd.timedelta_range("1 days 1 min", periods=5, freq="H"))
1918         td2 = td1.copy()
1919         td2.iloc[1] = np.nan
1920 
1921         result = dt1 + td1[0]
1922         exp = (dt1.dt.tz_localize(None) + td1[0]).dt.tz_localize(tz)
1923         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
1924 
1925         result = dt2 + td2[0]
1926         exp = (dt2.dt.tz_localize(None) + td2[0]).dt.tz_localize(tz)
1927         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
1928 
1929         # odd numpy behavior with scalar timedeltas
1930         result = td1[0] + dt1
1931         exp = (dt1.dt.tz_localize(None) + td1[0]).dt.tz_localize(tz)
1932         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
1933 
1934         result = td2[0] + dt2
1935         exp = (dt2.dt.tz_localize(None) + td2[0]).dt.tz_localize(tz)
1936         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
1937 
1938         result = dt1 - td1[0]
1939         exp = (dt1.dt.tz_localize(None) - td1[0]).dt.tz_localize(tz)
1940         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
1941         msg = "(bad|unsupported) operand type for unary"
1942         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
1943             td1[0] - dt1
1944 
1945         result = dt2 - td2[0]
1946         exp = (dt2.dt.tz_localize(None) - td2[0]).dt.tz_localize(tz)
1947         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
1948         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
1949             td2[0] - dt2
1950 
1951         result = dt1 + td1
1952         exp = (dt1.dt.tz_localize(None) + td1).dt.tz_localize(tz)
1953         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
1954 
1955         result = dt2 + td2
1956         exp = (dt2.dt.tz_localize(None) + td2).dt.tz_localize(tz)
1957         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
1958 
1959         result = dt1 - td1
1960         exp = (dt1.dt.tz_localize(None) - td1).dt.tz_localize(tz)
1961         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
1962 
1963         result = dt2 - td2
1964         exp = (dt2.dt.tz_localize(None) - td2).dt.tz_localize(tz)
1965         tm.assert_series_equal(result, exp)
1966         msg = "cannot (add|subtract)"
1967         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
1968             td1 - dt1
1969         with pytest.raises(TypeError, match=msg):
1970             td2 - dt2

2226     @pytest.mark.parametrize("op", [operator.add, operator.sub])
2227     def test_timedelta64_equal_timedelta_supported_ops(self, op):
2228         ser = Series(
2229             [
2230                 Timestamp("20130301"),
2231                 Timestamp("20130228 23:00:00"),
2232                 Timestamp("20130228 22:00:00"),
2233                 Timestamp("20130228 21:00:00"),
2234             ]
2235         )
2236 
2237         intervals = ["D", "h", "m", "s", "us"]
2238 
2239         def timedelta64(*args):
2240             # see casting notes in NumPy gh-12927
2241             return np.sum(list(starmap(np.timedelta64, zip(args, intervals))))
2242 
2243         for d, h, m, s, us in product(*([range(2)] * 5)):
2244             nptd = timedelta64(d, h, m, s, us)
2245             pytd = timedelta(days=d, hours=h, minutes=m, seconds=s, microseconds=us)
2246             lhs = op(ser, nptd)
2247             rhs = op(ser, pytd)
2248 
2249             tm.assert_series_equal(lhs, rhs)

2320     def test_ufunc_coercions(self):
2321         idx = date_range("2011-01-01", periods=3, freq="2D", name="x")
2322 
2323         delta = np.timedelta64(1, "D")
2324         exp = date_range("2011-01-02", periods=3, freq="2D", name="x")
2325         for result in [idx + delta, np.add(idx, delta)]:
2326             assert isinstance(result, DatetimeIndex)
2327             tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
2328             assert result.freq == "2D"
2329 
2330         exp = date_range("2010-12-31", periods=3, freq="2D", name="x")
2331 
2332         for result in [idx - delta, np.subtract(idx, delta)]:
2333             assert isinstance(result, DatetimeIndex)
2334             tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
2335             assert result.freq == "2D"
2336 
2337         # When adding/subtracting an ndarray (which has no .freq), the result
2338         #  does not infer freq
2339         idx = idx._with_freq(None)
2340         delta = np.array(
2341             [np.timedelta64(1, "D"), np.timedelta64(2, "D"), np.timedelta64(3, "D")]
2342         )
2343         exp = DatetimeIndex(["2011-01-02", "2011-01-05", "2011-01-08"], name="x")
2344 
2345         for result in [idx + delta, np.add(idx, delta)]:
2346             tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
2347             assert result.freq == exp.freq
2348 
2349         exp = DatetimeIndex(["2010-12-31", "2011-01-01", "2011-01-02"], name="x")
2350         for result in [idx - delta, np.subtract(idx, delta)]:
2351             assert isinstance(result, DatetimeIndex)
2352             tm.assert_index_equal(result, exp)
2353             assert result.freq == exp.freq

2355     def test_dti_add_series(self, tz_naive_fixture, names):
2356         # GH#13905
2357         tz = tz_naive_fixture
2358         index = DatetimeIndex(
2359             ["2016-06-28 05:30", "2016-06-28 05:31"], tz=tz, name=names[0]
2360         )
2361         ser = Series([Timedelta(seconds=5)] * 2, index=index, name=names[1])
2362         expected = Series(index + Timedelta(seconds=5), index=index, name=names[2])
2363 
2364         # passing name arg isn't enough when names[2] is None
2365         expected.name = names[2]
2366         assert expected.dtype == index.dtype
2367         result = ser + index
2368         tm.assert_series_equal(result, expected)
2369         result2 = index + ser
2370         tm.assert_series_equal(result2, expected)
2371 
2372         expected = index + Timedelta(seconds=5)
2373         result3 = ser.values + index
2374         tm.assert_index_equal(result3, expected)
2375         result4 = index + ser.values
2376         tm.assert_index_equal(result4, expected)

2450 def test_dt64arr_addsub_object_dtype_2d():
2451     # block-wise DataFrame operations will require operating on 2D
2452     #  DatetimeArray/TimedeltaArray, so check that specifically.
2453     dti = pd.date_range("1994-02-13", freq="2W", periods=4)
2454     dta = dti._data.reshape((4, 1))
2455 
2456     other = np.array([[pd.offsets.Day(n)] for n in range(4)])
2457     assert other.shape == dta.shape
2458 
2459     with tm.assert_produces_warning(PerformanceWarning):
2460         result = dta + other
2461     with tm.assert_produces_warning(PerformanceWarning):
2462         expected = (dta[:, 0] + other[:, 0]).reshape(-1, 1)
2463 
2464     assert isinstance(result, DatetimeArray)
2465     assert result.freq is None
2466     tm.assert_numpy_array_equal(result._data, expected._data)
2467 
2468     with tm.assert_produces_warning(PerformanceWarning):
2469         # Case where we expect to get a TimedeltaArray back
2470         result2 = dta - dta.astype(object)
2471 
2472     assert isinstance(result2, TimedeltaArray)
2473     assert result2.shape == (4, 1)
2474     assert result2.freq is None
2475     assert (result2.asi8 == 0).all()
